[I] A graphical text and directory diff and merge tool

[T] KDiff3 is a program that compares two or three text input files
[T] or directories, shows the differences line by line and character by
[T] character, provides an automatic merge facility and an integrated editor
[T] for comfortable solving of merge conflicts, and has an intuitive graphical
[T] user interface.

[U] https://kdiff3.sourceforge.net

[A] Joachim Eibl <joachim.eibl@gmx.de>
